South African President Cyril Ramaphosa delivers his speech during the 2023 state-of-the-nation address (SONA) at the Cape Town City Hall in Cape Town on February 9, 2023. AFP/Esa Alexander JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has declared a National State of Disaster over the electricity crisis with immediate effect. Ramaphosa made the announcement while delivering the State of the Nation Address on Thursday. READ:Â Members of Parliament arrive ahead of SONA 2023 He says the state of disaster will exempt critical infrastructure including hospitals and water treatment plants from rolling blackouts. Ramaphosa also says a Minister of Electricity in the Presidency will be appointed.